.index start-listener
.usage builtin-function
.syntax
(start-listener &optional (port $repl-listener-port))

.description 
Starts a secondary thread listening to the given TCP port number. A text
editor may send snippets of Kiezellisp code to this port to be executed. This is
feature is available in the kiezellisp-sublimetext download.

.see-also
.api
$repl-listener-port

